 sides with no pain and no visible loss of alignment.","Stops are quiet and controlled; exits are clean without false steps.","Coach can identify the intended angle or transition from the athlete’s shin and hip position."],"stop_signs":["Knee, groin, Achilles, hamstring, or low-back pain.","Loss of balance on two consecutive reps.","Noticeable limp, protective movement, or inability to decelerate safely.","Reaction drills become collisions or unsafe reaches."]}'::jsonb,
