  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Low Box Drop to Stick develops vertical force absorption before harder cuts for field and court athletes who need abrupt stops, quick redirection, and explosive reacceleration while preserving posture and joint alignment.","setup":["Use a flat, dry surface with enough clear space for the prescribed approach and exit.","Mark start, plant, stop, or exit targets with cones when needed.","Athlete starts tall enough to see the field but low enough to load hips and push the ground."],"execution_steps":["Execute the Low Box Drop to Stick with the stated focus: vertical force absorption before harder cuts.","Enter the rep with quiet feet and an active trunk; do not rush the setup.","Load the hip, knee, and ankle together; keep the foot tripod and knee tracking over the midfoot.","Finish by sticking, braking, or exiting with the first two steps clean and intentional.","Reset fully before the next rep so every attempt is a quality repetition, not conditioning by accident."],"coach_cues":["Brake before you turn.","Hips low, chest proud, eyes up.","Push the ground away; do not reach for the cone.","Quiet stick, violent exit.","Knee over midfoot; own the inside edge."],"athlete_cues":["Brake before you turn.","Hips low, chest proud, eyes up.","Push the ground away; do not reach for the cone."],"breathing_cues":["Exhale through the plant or stick.","Do not hold the breath during braking.","Recover with calm nasal breathing between high-intent reps."],"common_faults":["Extra gather steps before the plant.","Knee collapsing inside the foot during the stop or cut.","Torso rotating away from the intended exit.","Plant foot too narrow, too far ahead, or too turned out for the cut angle.","Turning the drill into conditioning volume instead of quality movement."],"quality_gate":["Athlete can repeat the rep on both sides with no pain and no visible loss of alignment.","Stops are quiet and controlled; exits are clean without false steps.","